Package InfrastructureManager.Modules.RemoteExecution.Output

Class SSHClient

java.lang.Object
InfrastructureManager.PlatformObject
InfrastructureManager.Modules.RemoteExecution.RemoteExecutionModuleObject
InfrastructureManager.Modules.RemoteExecution.Output.SSHClient
All Implemented Interfaces:
PlatformOutput
public class SSHClient
extends RemoteExecutionModuleObject
implements PlatformOutput
Class that represents interaction with remote terminals via SSH as an output of the platform.

This type of output is used for interacting with remote UNIX terminals (BASH) via SSH.

It provides the following functionalities:

- Execute commands in a remote machine (both sudo and normal) - Send files to a remote machine via SCP It uses the external JSch to allow for SSH connection

  • Method Details

    • execute

      public void execute​(java.lang.String response) throws SSHException
      Based on processed responses from the inputs executes the different functionalities
      Specified by:
      execute in interface PlatformOutput
      Parameters:
      response - Must be of the way "ssh COMMAND", and depending on the command receives additional parameters: - "execute": A display parameter (which can be "-b" for the remote command to be executed in the background or "-f" for the opposite) and a command to execute remotely (can have spaces). - "setUp": Hostname (address), SSH port on host, Username and Password in the remote machine. - "sendFile": Path to the local file to be sent and Path in the remote machine to send to
      Throws:
      SSHException - If the passed command is invalid or is missing parameters.
